This paper deals with the problem of 3D object detection from a single image, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel approach that involves training the pipeline end-to-end using back-propagation, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of uncertainty estimates, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL, in that order.
